experimental model techniques and equipment for flutterinvestigations . an outline is given of the uses of flutter models as anaid to the designer in the avoidance of flutter .  detailsare given of the different types and methods of constructionthat are used for flutter models and of thevarious test facilities that are available for high speedand low speed tests .the procedure followed in the u.k. for flutter clearanceof the full scale aircraft is described, and the valueof the electronic flutter simulator in this field isdiscussed .